{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"0yxxudkuzdpqhapvplegwxz","title":"API Security Best Practices - curity","desc":"","updated":1664849068850,"created":1654401998926,"custom":{},"fname":"dev.security.api-security-best-practices__curity","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"2b25bffde05e0983ceb4cc2b60e1169b","links":[],"anchors":{"always-use-a-gateway":{"type":"header","text":"Always Use a Gateway","value":"always-use-a-gateway","line":10,"column":0,"depth":1},"always-use-a-central-oauth-server":{"type":"header","text":"Always Use a Central OAuth Server","value":"always-use-a-central-oauth-server","line":12,"column":0,"depth":1},"only-use-json-web-tokens-internally":{"type":"header","text":"Only Use JSON Web Tokens Internally","value":"only-use-json-web-tokens-internally","line":14,"column":0,"depth":1},"use-scopes-for-coarse-grained-access-control":{"type":"header","text":"Use Scopes for Coarse-Grained Access Control","value":"use-scopes-for-coarse-grained-access-control","line":20,"column":0,"depth":1},"use-claims-for-fine-grained-access-control-at-the-api-level":{"type":"header","text":"Use Claims for Fine-Grained Access Control at the API Level","value":"use-claims-for-fine-grained-access-control-at-the-api-level","line":22,"column":0,"depth":1},"trust-no-one":{"type":"header","text":"Trust No One","value":"trust-no-one","line":24,"column":0,"depth":1},"create-or-reuse-libraries-for-jwt-validation":{"type":"header","text":"Create or Reuse Libraries for JWT Validation","value":"create-or-reuse-libraries-for-jwt-validation","line":26,"column":0,"depth":1},"do-not-mix-authentication-methods":{"type":"header","text":"Do Not Mix Authentication Methods","value":"do-not-mix-authentication-methods","line":28,"column":0,"depth":1},"protect-all-apis":{"type":"header","text":"Protect All APIs","value":"protect-all-apis","line":30,"column":0,"depth":1},"issue-jwts-for-internal-clients-inside-your-network":{"type":"header","text":"Issue JWTs for Internal Clients Inside Your Network","value":"issue-jwts-for-internal-clients-inside-your-network","line":32,"column":0,"depth":1},"use-json-web-key-sets-for-key-distribution":{"type":"header","text":"Use JSON Web Key Sets for Key Distribution","value":"use-json-web-key-sets-for-key-distribution","line":34,"column":0,"depth":1},"always-audit":{"type":"header","text":"Always Audit","value":"always-audit","line":36,"column":0,"depth":1},"manage-claims-centrally":{"type":"header","text":"Manage Claims Centrally","value":"manage-claims-centrally","line":38,"column":0,"depth":1},"abuse-doesnt-have-to-be-a-breach":{"type":"header","text":"Abuse Doesn't Have to Be a Breach","value":"abuse-doesnt-have-to-be-a-breach","line":40,"column":0,"depth":1}},"children":[],"parent":"NXAefr1pIXFjCcemglCJM","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"api-security-best-practices---curity\">API Security Best Practices - curity<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#api-security-best-practices---curity\"></a></h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://curity.io/resources/learn/api-security-best-practices/\">https://curity.io/resources/learn/api-security-best-practices/</a></p>\n<h1 id=\"always-use-a-gateway\">Always Use a Gateway<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#always-use-a-gateway\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"always-use-a-central-oauth-server\">Always Use a Central OAuth Server<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#always-use-a-central-oauth-server\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"only-use-json-web-tokens-internally\">Only Use JSON Web Tokens Internally<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#only-use-json-web-tokens-internally\"></a></h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://curity.io/resources/learn/phantom-token-pattern/\">Phantom Token Approach</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://curity.io/resources/learn/split-token-pattern/\">Split Token Approach</a></li>\n<li>Both involve an API Gateway in the process of translating an opaque token into a JWT.</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"use-scopes-for-coarse-grained-access-control\">Use Scopes for Coarse-Grained Access Control<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#use-scopes-for-coarse-grained-access-control\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"use-claims-for-fine-grained-access-control-at-the-api-level\">Use Claims for Fine-Grained Access Control at the API Level<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#use-claims-for-fine-grained-access-control-at-the-api-level\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"trust-no-one\">Trust No One<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#trust-no-one\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"create-or-reuse-libraries-for-jwt-validation\">Create or Reuse Libraries for JWT Validation<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#create-or-reuse-libraries-for-jwt-validation\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"do-not-mix-authentication-methods\">Do Not Mix Authentication Methods<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#do-not-mix-authentication-methods\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"protect-all-apis\">Protect All APIs<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#protect-all-apis\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"issue-jwts-for-internal-clients-inside-your-network\">Issue JWTs for Internal Clients Inside Your Network<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#issue-jwts-for-internal-clients-inside-your-network\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"use-json-web-key-sets-for-key-distribution\">Use JSON Web Key Sets for Key Distribution<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#use-json-web-key-sets-for-key-distribution\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"always-audit\">Always Audit<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#always-audit\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"manage-claims-centrally\">Manage Claims Centrally<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#manage-claims-centrally\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"abuse-doesnt-have-to-be-a-breach\">Abuse Doesn't Have to Be a Breach<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#abuse-doesnt-have-to-be-a-breach\"></a></h1>","noteIndex":{"id":"Iy0MoL0KnL55Br3AfTS2C","title":"Luke","desc":"","updated":1728366820262,"created":1644449449778,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"4e71d41370503c2c23fcde2ab3f6a266","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"Iy0MoL0KnL55Br3AfTS2C","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"life-tips","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":5,"offset":726},"end":{"line":19,"column":29,"offset":750},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"life-tips","anchorHeader":"wodenokoto"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"Iy0MoL0KnL55Br3AfTS2C","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"journal.what-i-read-in","alias":"What I read in 2024","position":{"start":{"line":44,"column":3,"offset":2019},"end":{"line":44,"column":49,"offset":2065},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"journal.what-i-read-in"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"Iy0MoL0KnL55Br3AfTS2C","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"journal.what-i-read-in.2023","alias":"2023","position":{"start":{"line":45,"column":5,"offset":2070},"end":{"line":45,"column":41,"offset":2106},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"journal.what-i-read-in.2023"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"Iy0MoL0KnL55Br3AfTS2C","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"journal.what-i-read-in.2022","alias":"2022","position":{"start":{"line":46,"column":5,"offset":2111},"end":{"line":46,"column":41,"offset":2147},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"journal.what-i-read-in.2022"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"Iy0MoL0KnL55Br3AfTS2C","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"journal.what-i-struggled-brag-in","position":{"start":{"line":52,"column":3,"offset":2283},"end":{"line":52,"column":39,"offset":2319},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"journal.what-i-struggled-brag-in"}}],"anchors":{"what-i-read-in-past":{"type":"header","text":"What I read in past","value":"what-i-read-in-past","line":48,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":["zd4mq442jike0pr0wba1u3m","g1fngdjl25nes6fs3lip602","ZbdkdApFqLdks4Moq92R9","5zn10cvj7ajy2gh2is5nqmg","4qo9ma0z0yu1czns6pxl7y5","ok0e729ho7o09xetujkxc0m","GR5x8HnNFEN6fU2UBSEIK","yirtnlj8q24yutcf3ss1xqy","eq0wc6t7wl2wv221yb68ro4","7x2fnv4j6gxts08qk0jguny","ettkt3iClONnxpbGwBVLl","hvh5bud6yp7dc89tuh95tr9","4fvoqrplw0cweo554usbjos","1swsbrhqi9jk41v9eodyi5q","SQqYupi6EFddTerBA8RRD","hjNeNc1F2JUh0lTWanH4h","qf0l4wbrc9jgooyzexmbq5v","gm64mijnozwjwlhp56luck7","q6bm7c2rod00klzhz85vbxw","7e1bpt9ytdq0wj77mt4vmud","fq13p8dc0rli9g1kdn0u8t9","1cssc3en59imsuocvyhppbf"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"\nHi there 👋. I'm a Front-end developer.\n\n---\n\n> I've often described my motivation for building software to others using imagery: I like to go find a secluded beach, build a large, magnificent sand castle, and then walk away. Will anyone notice? Probably not. Will the waves eventually destroy it? Yep. Did I still get immense satisfaction? Absolutely.\n>\n> — [aliasxneo](https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=41497113)\n\n> [The Rise of Worse is Better](https://www.dreamsongs.com/RiseOfWorseIsBetter.html)\n\n> “Motivation often comes after starting, not before. Action produces momentum.”\n>\n> — James Clear\n\n> Focus is more about **not** keeping busy when you need to wait for something.  \n> Eat the boredom for a minute.\n>\n> — [[life-tips#wodenokoto]]\n\n> [4 minutes run hard enough to push heart rate to 90%, 3 minutes recover, repeat 4 times](https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=34213181)\n>\n> - https://www.ntnu.edu/cerg/advice\n> - [Get running with Couch to 5K](https://www.nhs.uk/live-well/exercise/running-and-aerobic-exercises/get-running-with-couch-to-5k/)\n\n> [recommended routine - bodyweightfitness](https://www.reddit.com/r/bodyweightfitness/wiki/kb/recommended_routine/) - I Don't Have This Much Time!\n>\n> - Don't workout at all (saves anywhere from 20 to 60 minutes, but really, really, really, really, really, really, really, really, really not recommended)\n\n> [Just 4 pages a day. It really adds up.](https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=34779980)\n\n> I think it should be everyone's primary focus to sleep well, drink water, get outside, get active, and eat generally decently. I hate to say it, but if you're not eating a good amount of vegetables and fruit, decent protein, sleep, etc, no amount of XYZ will catch up to that detriment.\n>\n> — [CE02](https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=35056071)\n\n> Before leaving for the day I leave a comment in code: I’m working on this, need to do A, B C… to get it working.\n>\n> — [makz](https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=40744916)\n\n---\n\n## What I read in past\n\n- [[What I read in 2024|journal.what-i-read-in]]\n  - [[2023|journal.what-i-read-in.2023]]\n  - [[2022|journal.what-i-read-in.2022]]\n- 📝 [Gists](https://gist.github.com/Luke-SNAW)\n- 📜 [Journals](https://luke-snaw.github.io/Luke-SNAW__netlify-CMS.github.io/)\n\n---\n\n- [[journal.what-i-struggled-brag-in]]\n"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":5,"dev":{"enablePreviewV2":true},"commands":{"lookup":{"note":{"selectionMode":"extract","confirmVaultOnCreate":true,"vaultSelectionModeOnCreate":"smart","leaveTrace":false,"bubbleUpCreateNew":true,"fuzzThreshold":0.2}},"randomNote":{},"insertNoteLink":{"aliasMode":"none","enableMultiSelect":false},"insertNoteIndex":{"enableMarker":false},"copyNoteLink":{"aliasMode":"title"},"templateHierarchy":"template"},"workspace":{"vaults":[{"fsPath":"vault"}],"journal":{"dailyDomain":"daily","name":"journal","dateFormat":"y.MM.dd","addBehavior":"childOfDomain"},"scratch":{"name":"scratch","dateFormat":"y.MM.dd.HHmmss","addBehavior":"asOwnDomain"},"task":{"name":"","dateFormat":"","addBehavior":"childOfCurrent","statusSymbols":{"":" ","wip":"w","done":"x","assi